Dixon. London & Glasgow: Collins' Clear-Type Press, 1906.</p>

<p class="bibl">_____.  <span class="book">Christmas Books</span>. Illustrated by Harry 
Furniss. The Charles Dickens Library Edition. 18 vols. London: Educational Book, 1910.
Vol. VIII.</p>
 
<p class="bibl">_____.  <span class="book">Christmas Stories</span>. Illustrated by E. A. 
Abbey. The Household Edition. New York: Harper and Brothers, 1876.</p>

<p class="bibl">_____. <span class="book">The Cricket on the Hearth. A Fairy Tale of 
Home</span>. Illustrated by John Leech, Daniel Maclise, Richard Doyle, Clarkson 
Stanfield, and Edwin Landseer. Engraved by George Dalziel, Edward Dalziel, T. Williams,
J. Thompson, R. Graves, and Joseph Swain. London: Bradbury and Evans, 1846 [December
1845].</p>

<p class="bibl">_____. <span class="book">The Cricket on the Hearth</span>. Edited by 
